                    "question_id": 26785354,
                    "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26785354/normalizing-a-list-of-numbers-in-python/60480956#60480956",
                    "body": "<p><em>If working with data</em>, many times <code>pandas</code> is the simple key</p>\n\n<p>This particular code will put the <code>raw</code> into one column, then normalize by column per row. (But we can put it into a row and do it by row per column, too! Just have to change the <code>axis</code> values where 0 is for row and 1 is for column.)</p>\n\n<pre><code>import pandas as pd\n\n\nraw = [0.07, 0.14, 0.07]  \n\nraw_df = pd.DataFrame(raw)\nnormed_df = raw_df.div(raw_df.sum(axis=0), axis=1)\nnormed_df\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>where <code>normed_df</code> will display like:</p>\n\n<pre><code>    0\n0   0.25\n1   0.50\n2   0.25\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>and then can keep playing with the data, too!</p>\n"
