                    "body": "<p>For ones who wanna use <a href=\"https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/preprocessing.html#normalization\" rel=\"noreferrer\">scikit-learn</a>, you can use</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-py prettyprint-override\"><code>from sklearn.preprocessing import normalize\n\nx = [1,2,3,4]\nnormalize([x]) # array([[0.18257419, 0.36514837, 0.54772256, 0.73029674]])\nnormalize([x], norm=&quot;l1&quot;) # array([[0.1, 0.2, 0.3, 0.4]])\nnormalize([x], norm=&quot;max&quot;) # array([[0.25, 0.5 , 0.75, 1.]])\n</code></pre>\n"
