                    "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26785354/normalizing-a-list-of-numbers-in-python/66441175#66441175",
                    "body": "<p>Here is a not-terribly-inefficient one liner similar to the top answer (only performs summation once)</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-py prettyprint-override\"><code>norm = (lambda the_sum:[float(i)/the_sum for i in raw])(sum(raw))\n</code></pre>\n<p>A similar method can be done for a list with negative numbers</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-py prettyprint-override\"><code>norm = (lambda the_max, the_min: [(float(i)-the_min)/(the_max-the_min) for i in raw])(max(raw),min(raw))\n</code></pre>\n"
